  "subject": "Fix new cached rbac implementation",
  "commit_message": "Fix new cached rbac implementation\n\n- fix bug in new cached rbac implementation by skipping\n  the IdTokenExchangeFilterFunction for requests to Keycloak [0]\n- performance improvements for the implementation by reusing\n  parsed token from spring security instead of parsing a second time\n  in KeycloakPermissionFilter and using AntPathMatchers for matching\n  rbac excluded southbound endpoints\n- fix overly permissive path matching\n\n[0] all webclients inherit application wide filters.\n    IdTokenExchangeFilterFunction reads X-Auth-Identity from north\n    bound request. The northbound call that triggers the RBAC request\n    to keycloak does not have this header (and conceptually does not\n    need it/should not have it) and thus the extraction fails\n\nIssue-ID: PORTALNG-170\nChange-Id: Ib498b5195337609b2e7086c1af7c5b1dea872af7\nSigned-off-by: Fiete Ostkamp <fiete.ostkamp@telekom.de>\n",
